# {{AU}} {{slang}} (''possibly offensive'') A person with medium-dark skin, such as from the [[Middle East]].
# {{AU}} {{obsolete}} A [[militiaman]] or [[conscript]], short for [[chocolate soldier]].
#: 1942: ''Chocos with Hard Centres'' &mdash; Sydney Sun newspaper headline, 2 September 1942.  Quoted by Sidney J. Baker, ''The Australian Language'', second edition, 1966, chapter VIII section 3 (page 167).
===Usage notes===
The slang term for a dark skinned person may be used by such people themselves (the Australian television series ''[[w:Pizza (TV series)|Pizza]]'' made a good deal of fun with that for instance), but is generally considered racist when used otherwise.
